  - verses:
    - title: "Bildad\u2019s First Response to Job"
      content: 'Then Bildad the Shuhite replied to Job:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow long will you go on like this?\n\tYou sound like a blustering
        wind.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Does God twist justice?\n\tDoes the Almighty twist what is right?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your children must have sinned against him,\n\tso their punishment
        was well deserved.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if you pray to God\n\tand seek the favor of the Almighty,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and if you are pure and live with integrity,\n\the will surely rise
        up and restore your happy home.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And though you started with little,\n\tyou will end with much.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CJust ask the previous generation.\n\tPay attention to the experience
        of our ancestors.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For we were born but yesterday and know nothing.\n\tOur days on earth
        are as fleeting as a shadow.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But those who came before us will teach you.\n\tThey will teach you
        the wisdom of old.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCan papyrus reeds grow tall without a marsh?\n\tCan marsh grass
        flourish without water?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "While they are still flowering, not ready to be cut,\n\tthey begin
        to wither more quickly than grass.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The same happens to all who forget God.\n\tThe hopes of the godless
        evaporate.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their confidence hangs by a thread.\n\tThey are leaning on a spider\u2019s
        web.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They cling to their home for security, but it won\u2019t last.\n\tThey
        try to hold it tight, but it will not endure.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The godless seem like a lush plant growing in the sunshine,\n\tits
        branches spreading across the garden.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Its roots grow down through a pile of stones;\n\tit takes hold on
        a bed of rocks.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But when it is uprooted,\n\tit\u2019s as though it never existed!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That\u2019s the end of its life,\n\tand others spring up from the
        earth to replace it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut look, God will not reject a person of integrity,\n\tnor
        will he lend a hand to the wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will once again fill your mouth with laughter\n\tand your lips
        with shouts of joy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who hate you will be clothed with shame,\n\tand the home of
        the wicked will be destroyed.\u201D"
      comments: []
