        contents:
        - ft: 'An alternate reading in the Masoretic Text reads '
          body: God might kill me, but I hope in him.
    - title: 
      content: "But this is what will save me\u2014I am not godless.\n\tIf I were,
        I could not stand before him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen closely to what I am about to say.\n\tHear me out.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have prepared my case;\n\tI will be proved innocent.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who can argue with me over this?\n\tAnd if you prove me wrong, I
        will remain silent and die.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Job Asks How He Has Sinned
      content: "\u201CO God, grant me these two things,\n\tand then I will be able
        to face you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Remove your heavy hand from me,\n\tand don\u2019t terrify me with
        your awesome presence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now summon me, and I will answer!\n\tOr let me speak to you, and
        you reply.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Tell me, what have I done wrong?\n\tShow me my rebellion and my sin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why do you turn away from me?\n\tWhy do you treat me as your enemy?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Would you terrify a leaf blown by the wind?\n\tWould you chase dry
        straw?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou write bitter accusations against me\n\tand bring up all
        the sins of my youth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You put my feet in stocks.\n\tYou examine all my paths.\n\tYou trace
        all my footprints.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I waste away like rotting wood,\n\tlike a moth-eaten coat."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow frail is humanity!\n\tHow short is life, how full of trouble!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We blossom like a flower and then wither.\n\tLike a passing shadow,
        we quickly disappear.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Must you keep an eye on such a frail creature\n\tand demand an accounting
        from me?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who can bring purity out of an impure person?\n\tNo one!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have decided the length of our lives.\n\tYou know how many months
        we will live,\n\tand we are not given a minute longer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So leave us alone and let us rest!\n\tWe are like hired hands, so
        let us finish our work in peace.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEven a tree has more hope!\n\tIf it is cut down, it will sprout
        again\n\tand grow new branches.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Though its roots have grown old in the earth\n\tand its stump decays,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "at the scent of water it will bud\n\tand sprout again like a new
        seedling.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut when people die, their strength is gone.\n\tThey breathe
        their last, and then where are they?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As water evaporates from a lake\n\tand a river disappears in drought,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "people are laid to rest and do not rise again.\n\tUntil the heavens
        are no more, they will not wake up\n\tnor be roused from their sleep.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI wish you would hide me in the grave[COMMENT[0]]and forget
        me there until your anger has passed.\n\tBut mark your calendar to think
        of me again!  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: in Sheol.
    - title: 
      content: "Can the dead live again?\n\tIf so, this would give me hope through
        all my years of struggle,\n\tand I would eagerly await the release of death.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You would call and I would answer,\n\tand you would yearn for me,
        your handiwork.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For then you would guard my steps,\n\tinstead of watching for my
        sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My sins would be sealed in a pouch,\n\tand you would cover my guilt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut instead, as mountains fall and crumble\n\tand as rocks
        fall from a cliff,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "as water wears away the stones\n\tand floods wash away the soil,\n\tso
        you destroy people\u2019s hope.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You always overpower them, and they pass from the scene.\n\tYou disfigure
        them in death and send them away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They never know if their children grow up in honor\n\tor sink to
        insignificance.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They suffer painfully;\n\ttheir life is full of trouble.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Eliphaz\u2019s Second Response to Job"
      content: 'Then Eliphaz the Temanite replied:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CA wise man wouldn\u2019t answer with such empty talk!\n\tYou
        are nothing but a windbag.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The wise don\u2019t engage in empty chatter.\n\tWhat good are such
        words?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Have you no fear of God,\n\tno reverence for him?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your sins are telling your mouth what to say.\n\tYour words are based
        on clever deception.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your own mouth condemns you, not I.\n\tYour own lips testify against
        you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWere you the first person ever born?\n\tWere you born before
        the hills were made?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Were you listening at God\u2019s secret council?\n\tDo you have a
        monopoly on wisdom?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What do you know that we don\u2019t?\n\tWhat do you understand that
        we do not?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "On our side are aged, gray-haired men\n\tmuch older than your father!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIs God\u2019s comfort too little for you?\n\tIs his gentle
        word not enough?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What has taken away your reason?\n\tWhat has weakened your vision,[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'Why do your eyes flash with anger; '
        - ft: 'Hebrew reads '
          body: Why do your eyes blink.
    - title: 
      content: "that you turn against God\n\tand say all these evil things?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can any mortal be pure?\n\tCan anyone born of a woman be just?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look, God does not even trust the angels.[COMMENT[0]]Even the heavens
        are not absolutely pure in his sight.  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the holy ones.
    - title: 
      content: "How much less pure is a corrupt and sinful person\n\twith a thirst
        for wickedness!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf you will listen, I will show you.\n\tI will answer you from
        my own experience.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And it is confirmed by the reports of wise men\n\twho have heard
        the same thing from their fathers\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "from those to whom the land was given\n\tlong before any foreigners
        arrived.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe wicked writhe in pain throughout their lives.\n\tYears
        of trouble are stored up for the ruthless.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The sound of terror rings in their ears,\n\tand even on good days
        they fear the attack of the destroyer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They dare not go out into the darkness\n\tfor fear they will be murdered.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They wander around, saying, \u2018Where can I find bread?\u2019[COMMENT[0]]They
        know their day of destruction is near.  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:23 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: He is appointed to be food for a vulture.
    - title: 
      content: "That dark day terrifies them.\n\tThey live in distress and anguish,\n\tlike
        a king preparing for battle.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For they shake their fists at God,\n\tdefying the Almighty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Holding their strong shields,\n\tthey defiantly charge against him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThese wicked people are heavy and prosperous;\n\ttheir waists
        bulge with fat.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But their cities will be ruined.\n\tThey will live in abandoned houses\n\tthat
        are ready to tumble down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their riches will not last,\n\tand their wealth will not endure.\n\tTheir
        possessions will no longer spread across the horizon.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThey will not escape the darkness.\n\tThe burning sun will
        wither their shoots,\n\tand the breath of God will destroy them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let them no longer fool themselves by trusting in empty riches,\n\tfor
        emptiness will be their only reward.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will be cut down in the prime of life;\n\ttheir branches will
        never again be green.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will be like a vine whose grapes are harvested too early,\n\tlike
        an olive tree that loses its blossoms before the fruit can form.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the godless are barren.\n\tTheir homes, enriched through bribery,
        will burn.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They conceive trouble and give birth to evil.\n\tTheir womb produces
        deceit.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Fifth Speech: A Response to Eliphaz"
      content: 'Then Job spoke again:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have heard all this before.\n\tWhat miserable comforters
        you are!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Won\u2019t you ever stop blowing hot air?\n\tWhat makes you keep
        on talking?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I could say the same things if you were in my place.\n\tI could spout
        off criticism and shake my head at you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if it were me, I would encourage you.\n\tI would try to take
        away your grief.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Instead, I suffer if I defend myself,\n\tand I suffer no less if
        I refuse to speak.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO God, you have ground me down\n\tand devastated my family.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As if to prove I have sinned, you\u2019ve reduced me to skin and
        bones.\n\tMy gaunt flesh testifies against me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God hates me and angrily tears me apart.\n\tHe snaps his teeth at
        me\n\tand pierces me with his eyes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People jeer and laugh at me.\n\tThey slap my cheek in contempt.\n\tA
        mob gathers against me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God has handed me over to sinners.\n\tHe has tossed me into the hands
        of the wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI was living quietly until he shattered me.\n\tHe took me by
        the neck and broke me in pieces.\n\tThen he set me up as his target,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and now his archers surround me.\n\tHis arrows pierce me without
        mercy.\n\tThe ground is wet with my blood.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: my gall.
    - title: 
      content: "Again and again he smashes against me,\n\tcharging at me like a warrior.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I wear burlap to show my grief.\n\tMy pride lies in the dust.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My eyes are red with weeping;\n\tdark shadows circle my eyes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet I have done no wrong,\n\tand my prayer is pure.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO earth, do not conceal my blood.\n\tLet it cry out on my behalf.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even now my witness is in heaven.\n\tMy advocate is there on high.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My friends scorn me,\n\tbut I pour out my tears to God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I need someone to mediate between God and me,\n\tas a person mediates
        between friends.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For soon I must go down that road\n\tfrom which I will never return."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Job Continues to Defend His Innocence
      content: "\u201CMy spirit is crushed,\n\tand my life is nearly snuffed out.\n\tThe
        grave is ready to receive me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am surrounded by mockers.\n\tI watch how bitterly they taunt me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must defend my innocence, O God,\n\tsince no one else will
        stand up for me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have closed their minds to understanding,\n\tbut do not let them
        triumph.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They betray their friends for their own advantage,\n\tso let their
        children faint with hunger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGod has made a mockery of me among the people;\n\tthey spit
        in my face.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My eyes are swollen with weeping,\n\tand I am but a shadow of my
        former self.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The virtuous are horrified when they see me.\n\tThe innocent rise
        up against the ungodly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The righteous keep moving forward,\n\tand those with clean hands
        become stronger and stronger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAs for all of you, come back with a better argument,\n\tthough
        I still won\u2019t find a wise man among you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My days are over.\n\tMy hopes have disappeared.\n\tMy heart\u2019s
        desires are broken.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These men say that night is day;\n\tthey claim that the darkness
        is light.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What if I go to the grave[COMMENT[0]]and make my bed in darkness?  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'to Sheol; '
        - ft: also in 17:16.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "What if I call the grave my father,\n\tand the maggot my mother or
        my sister?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Where then is my hope?\n\tCan anyone find it?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No, my hope will go down with me to the grave.\n\tWe will rest together
        in the dust!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Bildad\u2019s Second Response to Job"
      content: 'Then Bildad the Shuhite replied:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow long before you stop talking?\n\tSpeak sense if you want
        us to answer!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do you think we are mere animals?\n\tDo you think we are stupid?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You may tear out your hair in anger,\n\tbut will that destroy the
        earth?\n\tWill it make the rocks tremble?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSurely the light of the wicked will be snuffed out.\n\tThe
        sparks of their fire will not glow.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The light in their tent will grow dark.\n\tThe lamp hanging above
        them will be quenched.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The confident stride of the wicked will be shortened.\n\tTheir own
        schemes will be their downfall.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The wicked walk into a net.\n\tThey fall into a pit.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A trap grabs them by the heel.\n\tA snare holds them tight.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A noose lies hidden on the ground.\n\tA rope is stretched across
        their path.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTerrors surround the wicked\n\tand trouble them at every step.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hunger depletes their strength,\n\tand calamity waits for them to
        stumble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Disease eats their skin;\n\tdeath devours their limbs.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are torn from the security of their homes\n\tand are brought
        down to the king of terrors.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The homes of the wicked will burn down;\n\tburning sulfur rains on
        their houses.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their roots will dry up,\n\tand their branches will wither.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All memory of their existence will fade from the earth;\n\tno one
        will remember their names.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will be thrust from light into darkness,\n\tdriven from the
        world.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will have neither children nor grandchildren,\n\tnor any survivor
        in the place where they lived.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People in the west are appalled at their fate;\n\tpeople in the east
        are horrified.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will say, \u2018This was the home of a wicked person,\n\tthe
        place of one who rejected God.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Sixth Speech: A Response to Bildad"
      content: 'Then Job spoke again:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow long will you torture me?\n\tHow long will you try to crush
        me with your words?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have already insulted me ten times.\n\tYou should be ashamed
        of treating me so badly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even if I have sinned,\n\tthat is my concern, not yours.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You think you\u2019re better than I am,\n\tusing my humiliation as
        evidence of my sin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But it is God who has wronged me,\n\tcapturing me in his net.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: for I am like a city under siege.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI cry out, \u2018Help!\u2019 but no one answers me.\n\tI protest,
        but there is no justice.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God has blocked my way so I cannot move.\n\tHe has plunged my path
        into darkness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He has stripped me of my honor\n\tand removed the crown from my head.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He has demolished me on every side, and I am finished.\n\tHe has
        uprooted my hope like a fallen tree.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "His fury burns against me;\n\the counts me as an enemy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "His troops advance.\n\tThey build up roads to attack me.\n\tThey
        camp all around my tent.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy relatives stay far away,\n\tand my friends have turned against
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My family is gone,\n\tand my close friends have forgotten me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My servants and maids consider me a stranger.\n\tI am like a foreigner
        to them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When I call my servant, he doesn\u2019t come;\n\tI have to plead
        with him!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My breath is repulsive to my wife.\n\tI am rejected by my own family.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even young children despise me.\n\tWhen I stand to speak, they turn
        their backs on me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My close friends detest me.\n\tThose I loved have turned against
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have been reduced to skin and bones\n\tand have escaped death by
        the skin of my teeth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave mercy on me, my friends, have mercy,\n\tfor the hand of
        God has struck me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Must you also persecute me, like God does?\n\tHaven\u2019t you chewed
        me up enough?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COh, that my words could be recorded.\n\tOh, that they could
        be inscribed on a monument,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "carved with an iron chisel and filled with lead,\n\tengraved forever
        in the rock.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut as for me, I know that my Redeemer lives,\n\tand he will
        stand upon the earth at last.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And after my body has decayed,\n\tyet in my body I will see God![COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:26 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'without my body I will see God. '
        - ft: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "I will see him for myself.\n\tYes, I will see him with my own eyes.\n\tI
        am overwhelmed at the thought!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow dare you go on persecuting me,\n\tsaying, \u2018It\u2019s
        his own fault\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You should fear punishment yourselves,\n\tfor your attitude deserves
        punishment.\n\tThen you will know that there is indeed a judgment.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Zophar\u2019s Second Response to Job"
      content: 'Then Zophar the Naamathite replied:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI must reply\n\tbecause I am greatly disturbed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I\u2019ve had to endure your insults,\n\tbut now my spirit prompts
        me to reply.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t you realize that from the beginning of time,\n\tever
        since people were first placed on the earth,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the triumph of the wicked has been short lived\n\tand the joy of
        the godless has been only temporary?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Though the pride of the godless reaches to the heavens\n\tand their
        heads touch the clouds,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "yet they will vanish forever,\n\tthrown away like their own dung.\n\tThose
        who knew them will ask,\n\t\u2018Where are they?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will fade like a dream and not be found.\n\tThey will vanish
        like a vision in the night.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who once saw them will see them no more.\n\tTheir families
        will never see them again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their children will beg from the poor,\n\tfor they must give back
        their stolen riches.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Though they are young,\n\ttheir bones will lie in the dust.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThey enjoyed the sweet taste of wickedness,\n\tletting it melt
        under their tongue.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They savored it,\n\tholding it long in their mouths.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But suddenly the food in their bellies turns sour,\n\ta poisonous
        venom in their stomach.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will vomit the wealth they swallowed.\n\tGod won\u2019t let
        them keep it down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will suck the poison of cobras.\n\tThe viper will kill them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will never again enjoy streams of olive oil\n\tor rivers of
        milk and honey.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will give back everything they worked for.\n\tTheir wealth will
        bring them no joy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For they oppressed the poor and left them destitute.\n\tThey foreclosed
        on their homes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They were always greedy and never satisfied.\n\tNothing remains of
        all the things they dreamed about.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Nothing is left after they finish gorging themselves.\n\tTherefore,
        their prosperity will not endure.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn the midst of plenty, they will run into trouble\n\tand be
        overcome by misery.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "May God give them a bellyful of trouble.\n\tMay God rain down his
        anger upon them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When they try to escape an iron weapon,\n\ta bronze-tipped arrow
        will pierce them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The arrow is pulled from their back,\n\tand the arrowhead glistens
        with blood.[COMMENT[0]]The terrors of death are upon them.  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:25 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: with gall.
    - title: 
      content: "Their treasures will be thrown into deepest darkness.\n\tA wildfire
        will devour their goods,\n\tconsuming all they have left.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The heavens will reveal their guilt,\n\tand the earth will testify
        against them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A flood will sweep away their house.\n\tGod\u2019s anger will descend
        on them in torrents.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is the reward that God gives the wicked.\n\tIt is the inheritance
        decreed by God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Seventh Speech: A Response to Zophar"
      content: 'Then Job spoke again:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen closely to what I am saying.\n\tThat\u2019s one consolation
        you can give me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Bear with me, and let me speak.\n\tAfter I have spoken, you may resume
        mocking me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy complaint is with God, not with people.\n\tI have good reason
        to be so impatient.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look at me and be stunned.\n\tPut your hand over your mouth in shock.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When I think about what I am saying, I shudder.\n\tMy body trembles.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhy do the wicked prosper,\n\tgrowing old and powerful?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They live to see their children grow up and settle down,\n\tand they
        enjoy their grandchildren.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their homes are safe from every fear,\n\tand God does not punish
        them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their bulls never fail to breed.\n\tTheir cows bear calves and never
        miscarry.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They let their children frisk about like lambs.\n\tTheir little ones
        skip and dance.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They sing with tambourine and harp.\n\tThey celebrate to the sound
        of the flute.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They spend their days in prosperity,\n\tthen go down to the grave[COMMENT[0]]
        in peace.  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to Sheol.
    - title: 
      content: "And yet they say to God, \u2018Go away.\n\tWe want no part of you
        and your ways.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who is the Almighty, and why should we obey him?\n\tWhat good will
        it do us to pray?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "(They think their prosperity is of their own doing,\n\tbut I will
        have nothing to do with that kind of thinking.)  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYet the light of the wicked never seems to be extinguished.\n\tDo
        they ever have trouble?\n\tDoes God distribute sorrows to them in anger?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Are they driven before the wind like straw?\n\tAre they carried away
        by the storm like chaff?\n\tNot at all!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018Well,\u2019 you say, \u2018at least God will punish their
        children!\u2019\n\tBut I say he should punish the ones who sin,\n\tso that
        they understand his judgment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let them see their destruction with their own eyes.\n\tLet them drink
        deeply of the anger of the Almighty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For they will not care what happens to their family\n\tafter they
        are dead.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut who can teach a lesson to God,\n\tsince he judges even
        the most powerful?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "One person dies in prosperity,\n\tcompletely comfortable and secure,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the picture of good health,\n\tvigorous and fit.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Another person dies in bitter poverty,\n\tnever having tasted the
        good life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But both are buried in the same dust,\n\tboth eaten by the same maggots.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook, I know what you\u2019re thinking.\n\tI know the schemes
        you plot against me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will tell me of rich and wicked people\n\twhose houses have vanished
        because of their sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But ask those who have been around,\n\tand they will tell you the
        truth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Evil people are spared in times of calamity\n\tand are allowed to
        escape disaster.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No one criticizes them openly\n\tor pays them back for what they
        have done.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When they are carried to the grave,\n\tan honor guard keeps watch
        at their tomb.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A great funeral procession goes to the cemetery.\n\tMany pay their
        respects as the body is laid to rest,\n\tand the earth gives sweet repose.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow can your empty clich\xE9s comfort me?\n\tAll your explanations
        are lies!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Eliphaz\u2019s Third Response to Job"
      content: 'Then Eliphaz the Temanite replied:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCan a person do anything to help God?\n\tCan even a wise person
        be helpful to him?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Is it any advantage to the Almighty if you are righteous?\n\tWould
        it be any gain to him if you were perfect?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Is it because you\u2019re so pious that he accuses you\n\tand brings
        judgment against you?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No, it\u2019s because of your wickedness!\n\tThere\u2019s no limit
        to your sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor example, you must have lent money to your friend\n\tand
        demanded clothing as security.\n\tYes, you stripped him to the bone.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You must have refused water for the thirsty\n\tand food for the hungry.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You probably think the land belongs to the powerful\n\tand only the
        privileged have a right to it!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You must have sent widows away empty-handed\n\tand crushed the hopes
        of orphans.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why you are surrounded by traps\n\tand tremble from sudden
        fears.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why you cannot see in the darkness,\n\tand waves of water
        cover you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGod is so great\u2014higher than the heavens,\n\thigher than
        the farthest stars.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you reply, \u2018That\u2019s why God can\u2019t see what I am
        doing!\n\tHow can he judge through the thick darkness?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For thick clouds swirl about him, and he cannot see us.\n\tHe is
        way up there, walking on the vault of heaven.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWill you continue on the old paths\n\twhere evil people have
        walked?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They were snatched away in the prime of life,\n\tthe foundations
        of their lives washed away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For they said to God, \u2018Leave us alone!\n\tWhat can the Almighty
        do to us?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet he was the one who filled their homes with good things,\n\tso
        I will have nothing to do with that kind of thinking.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe righteous will be happy to see the wicked destroyed,\n\tand
        the innocent will laugh in contempt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will say, \u2018See how our enemies have been destroyed.\n\tThe
        last of them have been consumed in the fire.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSubmit to God, and you will have peace;\n\tthen things will
        go well for you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to his instructions,\n\tand store them in your heart.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you return to the Almighty, you will be restored\u2014\n\tso clean
        up your life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you give up your lust for money\n\tand throw your precious gold
        into the river,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the Almighty himself will be your treasure.\n\tHe will be your precious
        silver!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen you will take delight in the Almighty\n\tand look up to
        God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will pray to him, and he will hear you,\n\tand you will fulfill
        your vows to him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will succeed in whatever you choose to do,\n\tand light will
        shine on the road ahead of you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If people are in trouble and you say, \u2018Help them,\u2019\n\tGod
        will save them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even sinners will be rescued;\n\tthey will be rescued because your
        hands are pure.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Eighth Speech: A Response to Eliphaz"
      content: 'Then Job spoke again:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy complaint today is still a bitter one,\n\tand I try hard
        not to groan aloud.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If only I knew where to find God,\n\tI would go to his court.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I would lay out my case\n\tand present my arguments.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I would listen to his reply\n\tand understand what he says to
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Would he use his great power to argue with me?\n\tNo, he would give
        me a fair hearing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Honest people can reason with him,\n\tso I would be forever acquitted
        by my judge.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I go east, but he is not there.\n\tI go west, but I cannot find him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I do not see him in the north, for he is hidden.\n\tI look to the
        south, but he is concealed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut he knows where I am going.\n\tAnd when he tests me, I will
        come out as pure as gold.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I have stayed on God\u2019s paths;\n\tI have followed his ways
        and not turned aside.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have not departed from his commands,\n\tbut have treasured his
        words more than daily food.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But once he has made his decision, who can change his mind?\n\tWhatever
        he wants to do, he does.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So he will do to me whatever he has planned.\n\tHe controls my destiny.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No wonder I am so terrified in his presence.\n\tWhen I think of it,
        terror grips me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God has made me sick at heart;\n\tthe Almighty has terrified me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Darkness is all around me;\n\tthick, impenetrable darkness is everywhere."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Job Asks Why the Wicked Are Not Punished
      content: "\u201CWhy doesn\u2019t the Almighty bring the wicked to judgment?\n\tWhy
        must the godly wait for him in vain?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Evil people steal land by moving the boundary markers.\n\tThey steal
        livestock and put them in their own pastures.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They take the orphan\u2019s donkey\n\tand demand the widow\u2019s
        ox as security for a loan.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The poor are pushed off the path;\n\tthe needy must hide together
        for safety.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Like wild donkeys in the wilderness,\n\tthe poor must spend all their
        time looking for food,\n\tsearching even in the desert for food for their
        children.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They harvest a field they do not own,\n\tand they glean in the vineyards
        of the wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All night they lie naked in the cold,\n\twithout clothing or covering.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are soaked by mountain showers,\n\tand they huddle against the
        rocks for want of a home.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe wicked snatch a widow\u2019s child from her breast,\n\ttaking
        the baby as security for a loan.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The poor must go about naked, without any clothing.\n\tThey harvest
        food for others while they themselves are starving.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They press out olive oil without being allowed to taste it,\n\tand
        they tread in the winepress as they suffer from thirst.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The groans of the dying rise from the city,\n\tand the wounded cry
        for help,\n\tyet God ignores their moaning.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWicked people rebel against the light.\n\tThey refuse to acknowledge
        its ways\n\tor stay in its paths.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The murderer rises in the early dawn\n\tto kill the poor and needy;\n\tat
        night he is a thief.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The adulterer waits for the twilight,\n\tsaying, \u2018No one will
        see me then.\u2019\n\tHe hides his face so no one will know him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Thieves break into houses at night\n\tand sleep in the daytime.\n\tThey
        are not acquainted with the light.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The black night is their morning.\n\tThey ally themselves with the
        terrors of the darkness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut they disappear like foam down a river.\n\tEverything they
        own is cursed,\n\tand they are afraid to enter their own vineyards.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The grave[COMMENT[0]] consumes sinners\n\tjust as drought and heat
        consume snow.  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Sheol.
    - title: 
      content: "Their own mothers will forget them.\n\tMaggots will find them sweet
        to eat.\n\tNo one will remember them.\n\tWicked people are broken like a
        tree in the storm.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They cheat the woman who has no son to help her.\n\tThey refuse to
        help the needy widow.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGod, in his power, drags away the rich.\n\tThey may rise high,
        but they have no assurance of life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They may be allowed to live in security,\n\tbut God is always watching
        them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And though they are great now,\n\tin a moment they will be gone like
        all others,\n\tcut off like heads of grain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can anyone claim otherwise?\n\tWho can prove me wrong?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Bildad\u2019s Third Response to Job"
      content: 'Then Bildad the Shuhite replied:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGod is powerful and dreadful.\n\tHe enforces peace in the heavens.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who is able to count his heavenly army?\n\tDoesn\u2019t his light
        shine on all the earth?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How can a mortal be innocent before God?\n\tCan anyone born of a
        woman be pure?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God is more glorious than the moon;\n\the shines brighter than the
        stars.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In comparison, people are maggots;\n\twe mortals are mere worms.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Ninth Speech: A Response to Bildad"
      content: 'Then Job spoke again:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow you have helped the powerless!\n\tHow you have saved the
        weak!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How you have enlightened my stupidity!\n\tWhat wise advice you have
        offered!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Where have you gotten all these wise sayings?\n\tWhose spirit speaks
        through you?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe dead tremble\u2014\n\tthose who live beneath the waters.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The underworld[COMMENT[0]] is naked in God\u2019s presence.\n\tThe
        place of destruction[COMMENT[1]] is uncovered.  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:6a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Sheol.
      - number: '26:6b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Abaddon.
    - title: 
      content: "God stretches the northern sky over empty space\n\tand hangs the
        earth on nothing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He wraps the rain in his thick clouds,\n\tand the clouds don\u2019t
        burst with the weight.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He covers the face of the moon,[COMMENT[0]]shrouding it with his
        clouds.  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: covers his throne.
    - title: 
      content: "He created the horizon when he separated the waters;\n\the set the
        boundary between day and night.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The foundations of heaven tremble;\n\tthey shudder at his rebuke.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "By his power the sea grew calm.\n\tBy his skill he crushed the great
        sea monster.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Rahab, '
        - ft: the name of a mythical sea monster that represents chaos in ancient
            literature.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "His Spirit made the heavens beautiful,\n\tand his power pierced the
        gliding serpent.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These are just the beginning of all that he does,\n\tmerely a whisper
        of his power.\n\tWho, then, can comprehend the thunder of his power?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Final Speech"
      content: 'Job continued speaking:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI vow by the living God, who has taken away my rights,\n\tby
        the Almighty who has embittered my soul\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As long as I live,\n\twhile I have breath from God,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "my lips will speak no evil,\n\tand my tongue will speak no lies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will never concede that you are right;\n\tI will defend my integrity
        until I die.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will maintain my innocence without wavering.\n\tMy conscience is
        clear for as long as I live.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMay my enemy be punished like the wicked,\n\tmy adversary like
        those who do evil.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For what hope do the godless have when God cuts them off\n\tand takes
        away their life?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Will God listen to their cry\n\twhen trouble comes upon them?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can they take delight in the Almighty?\n\tCan they call to God at
        any time?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will teach you about God\u2019s power.\n\tI will not conceal anything
        concerning the Almighty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you have seen all this,\n\tyet you say all these useless things
        to me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the wicked will receive from God;\n\tthis is their
        inheritance from the Almighty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They may have many children,\n\tbut the children will die in war
        or starve to death.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who survive will die of a plague,\n\tand not even their widows
        will mourn them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEvil people may have piles of money\n\tand may store away mounds
        of clothing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the righteous will wear that clothing,\n\tand the innocent will
        divide that money.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The wicked build houses as fragile as a spider\u2019s web,[COMMENT[0]]as
        flimsy as a shelter made of branches.  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek and Syriac versions (see also 8:14); Hebrew reads '
          body: a moth.
    - title: 
      content: "The wicked go to bed rich\n\tbut wake to find that all their wealth
        is gone.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Terror overwhelms them like a flood,\n\tand they are blown away in
        the storms of the night.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The east wind carries them away, and they are gone.\n\tIt sweeps
        them away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It whirls down on them without mercy.\n\tThey struggle to flee from
        its power.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But everyone jeers at them\n\tand mocks them."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Job Speaks of Wisdom and Understanding
      content: "\u201CPeople know where to mine silver\n\tand how to refine gold.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They know where to dig iron from the earth\n\tand how to smelt copper
        from rock.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They know how to shine light in the darkness\n\tand explore the farthest
        regions of the earth\n\tas they search in the dark for ore.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They sink a mine shaft into the earth\n\tfar from where anyone lives.\n\tThey
        descend on ropes, swinging back and forth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Food is grown on the earth above,\n\tbut down below, the earth is
        melted as by fire.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Here the rocks contain precious lapis lazuli,\n\tand the dust contains
        gold.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These are treasures no bird of prey can see,\n\tno falcon\u2019s
        eye observe.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No wild animal has walked upon these treasures;\n\tno lion has ever
        set his paw there.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People know how to tear apart flinty rocks\n\tand overturn the roots
        of mountains.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They cut tunnels in the rocks\n\tand uncover precious stones.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They dam up the trickling streams\n\tand bring to light the hidden
        treasures.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut do people know where to find wisdom?\n\tWhere can they
        find understanding?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No one knows where to find it,[COMMENT[0]]for it is not found among
        the living.  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads '
          body: knows its value.
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018It is not here,\u2019 says the ocean.\n\t\u2018Nor is it here,\u2019
        says the sea.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It cannot be bought with gold.\n\tIt cannot be purchased with silver.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It\u2019s worth more than all the gold of Ophir,\n\tgreater than
        precious onyx or lapis lazuli.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Wisdom is more valuable than gold and crystal.\n\tIt cannot be purchased
        with jewels mounted in fine gold.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Coral and jasper are worthless in trying to get it.\n\tThe price
        of wisdom is far above rubies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Precious peridot from Ethiopia[COMMENT[0]] cannot be exchanged for
        it.\n\tIt\u2019s worth more than the purest gold.  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: from Cush.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut do people know where to find wisdom?\n\tWhere can they
        find understanding?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is hidden from the eyes of all humanity.\n\tEven the sharp-eyed
        birds in the sky cannot discover it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Destruction[COMMENT[0]] and Death say,\n\t\u2018We\u2019ve heard
        only rumors of where wisdom can be found.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:22 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Abaddon.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGod alone understands the way to wisdom;\n\the knows where
        it can be found,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for he looks throughout the whole earth\n\tand sees everything under
        the heavens.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He decided how hard the winds should blow\n\tand how much rain should
        fall.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He made the laws for the rain\n\tand laid out a path for the lightning.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he saw wisdom and evaluated it.\n\tHe set it in place and examined
        it thoroughly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And this is what he says to all humanity:\n\t\u2018The fear of the
        Lord is true wisdom;\n\tto forsake evil is real understanding.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Job Speaks of His Former Blessings
      content: 'Job continued speaking:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI long for the years gone by\n\twhen God took care of me,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "when he lit up the way before me\n\tand I walked safely through the
        darkness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When I was in my prime,\n\tGod\u2019s friendship was felt in my home.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Almighty was still with me,\n\tand my children were around me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My steps were awash in cream,\n\tand the rocks gushed olive oil for
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThose were the days when I went to the city gate\n\tand took
        my place among the honored leaders.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The young stepped aside when they saw me,\n\tand even the aged rose
        in respect at my coming.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The princes stood in silence\n\tand put their hands over their mouths.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The highest officials of the city stood quietly,\n\tholding their
        tongues in respect.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAll who heard me praised me.\n\tAll who saw me spoke well of
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I assisted the poor in their need\n\tand the orphans who required
        help.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I helped those without hope, and they blessed me.\n\tAnd I caused
        the widows\u2019 hearts to sing for joy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Everything I did was honest.\n\tRighteousness covered me like a robe,\n\tand
        I wore justice like a turban.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I served as eyes for the blind\n\tand feet for the lame.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was a father to the poor\n\tand assisted strangers who needed help.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I broke the jaws of godless oppressors\n\tand plucked their victims
        from their teeth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI thought, \u2018Surely I will die surrounded by my family\n\tafter
        a long, good life.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '29:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: after I have counted my days like sand.
    - title: 
      content: "For I am like a tree whose roots reach the water,\n\twhose branches
        are refreshed with the dew.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "New honors are constantly bestowed on me,\n\tand my strength is continually
        renewed.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEveryone listened to my advice.\n\tThey were silent as they
        waited for me to speak.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And after I spoke, they had nothing to add,\n\tfor my counsel satisfied
        them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They longed for me to speak as people long for rain.\n\tThey drank
        my words like a refreshing spring rain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When they were discouraged, I smiled at them.\n\tMy look of approval
        was precious to them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Like a chief, I told them what to do.\n\tI lived like a king among
        his troops\n\tand comforted those who mourned."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Job Speaks of His Anguish
      content: "\u201CBut now I am mocked by people younger than I,\n\tby young men
        whose fathers are not worthy to run with my sheepdogs.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A lot of good they are to me\u2014\n\tthose worn-out wretches!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are gaunt from poverty and hunger.\n\tThey claw the dry ground
        in desolate wastelands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They pluck wild greens from among the bushes\n\tand eat from the
        roots of broom trees.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are driven from human society,\n\tand people shout at them as
        if they were thieves.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So now they live in frightening ravines,\n\tin caves and among the
        rocks.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They sound like animals howling among the bushes,\n\thuddled together
        beneath the nettles.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are nameless fools,\n\toutcasts from society.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd now they mock me with vulgar songs!\n\tThey taunt me!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They despise me and won\u2019t come near me,\n\texcept to spit in
        my face.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For God has cut my bowstring.\n\tHe has humbled me,\n\tso they have
        thrown off all restraint.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These outcasts oppose me to my face.\n\tThey send me sprawling\n\tand
        lay traps in my path.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They block my road\n\tand do everything they can to destroy me.\n\tThey
        know I have no one to help me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They come at me from all directions.\n\tThey jump on me when I am
        down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I live in terror now.\n\tMy honor has blown away in the wind,\n\tand
        my prosperity has vanished like a cloud.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd now my life seeps away.\n\tDepression haunts my days.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At night my bones are filled with pain,\n\twhich gnaws at me relentlessly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'With a strong hand, God grabs my shirt.[COMMENT[0]]He grips me by
        the collar of my coat.  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads '
          body: hand, my garment is disfigured.
    - title: 
      content: "He has thrown me into the mud.\n\tI\u2019m nothing more than dust
        and ashes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI cry to you, O God, but you don\u2019t answer.\n\tI stand
        before you, but you don\u2019t even look.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have become cruel toward me.\n\tYou use your power to persecute
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You throw me into the whirlwind\n\tand destroy me in the storm.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I know you are sending me to my death\u2014\n\tthe destination
        of all who live.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSurely no one would turn against the needy\n\twhen they cry
        for help in their trouble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Did I not weep for those in trouble?\n\tWas I not deeply grieved
        for the needy?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I looked for good, but evil came instead.\n\tI waited for the
        light, but darkness fell.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My heart is troubled and restless.\n\tDays of suffering torment me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I walk in gloom, without sunlight.\n\tI stand in the public square
        and cry for help.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Instead, I am considered a brother to jackals\n\tand a companion
        to owls.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My skin has turned dark,\n\tand my bones burn with fever.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My harp plays sad music,\n\tand my flute accompanies those who weep."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Final Protest of Innocence"
      content: "\u201CI made a covenant with my eyes\n\tnot to look with lust at
        a young woman.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For what has God above chosen for us?\n\tWhat is our inheritance
        from the Almighty on high?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Isn\u2019t it calamity for the wicked\n\tand misfortune for those
        who do evil?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Doesn\u2019t he see everything I do\n\tand every step I take?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave I lied to anyone\n\tor deceived anyone?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let God weigh me on the scales of justice,\n\tfor he knows my integrity.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If I have strayed from his pathway,\n\tor if my heart has lusted
        for what my eyes have seen,\n\tor if I am guilty of any other sin,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "then let someone else eat the crops I have planted.\n\tLet all that
        I have planted be uprooted.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf my heart has been seduced by a woman,\n\tor if I have lusted
        for my neighbor\u2019s wife,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "then let my wife serve[COMMENT[0]] another man;\n\tlet other men
        sleep with her.  "
      comments:
      - number: '31:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: grind for.
    - title: 
      content: "For lust is a shameful sin,\n\ta crime that should be punished.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is a fire that burns all the way to hell.[COMMENT[0]]It would
        wipe out everything I own.  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to Abaddon.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf I have been unfair to my male or female servants\n\twhen
        they brought their complaints to me,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "how could I face God?\n\tWhat could I say when he questioned me?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For God created both me and my servants.\n\tHe created us both in
        the womb.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave I refused to help the poor,\n\tor crushed the hopes of
        widows?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Have I been stingy with my food\n\tand refused to share it with orphans?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No, from childhood I have cared for orphans like a father,\n\tand
        all my life I have cared for widows.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Whenever I saw the homeless without clothes\n\tand the needy with
        nothing to wear,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "did they not praise me\n\tfor providing wool clothing to keep them
        warm?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf I raised my hand against an orphan,\n\tknowing the judges
        would take my side,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "then let my shoulder be wrenched out of place!\n\tLet my arm be torn
        from its socket!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That would be better than facing God\u2019s judgment.\n\tFor if the
        majesty of God opposes me, what hope is there?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave I put my trust in money\n\tor felt secure because of my
        gold?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Have I gloated about my wealth\n\tand all that I own?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave I looked at the sun shining in the skies,\n\tor the moon
        walking down its silver pathway,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and been secretly enticed in my heart\n\tto throw kisses at them
        in worship?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If so, I should be punished by the judges,\n\tfor it would mean I
        had denied the God of heaven.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave I ever rejoiced when disaster struck my enemies,\n\tor
        become excited when harm came their way?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No, I have never sinned by cursing anyone\n\tor by asking for revenge.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy servants have never said,\n\t\u2018He let others go hungry.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have never turned away a stranger\n\tbut have opened my doors to
        everyone.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave I tried to hide my sins like other people do,\n\tconcealing
        my guilt in my heart?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Have I feared the crowd\n\tor the contempt of the masses,\n\tso that
        I kept quiet and stayed indoors?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf only someone would listen to me!\n\tLook, I will sign my
        name to my defense.\n\tLet the Almighty answer me.\n\tLet my accuser write
        out the charges against me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I would face the accusation proudly.\n\tI would wear it like a crown.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I would tell him exactly what I have done.\n\tI would come before
        him like a prince.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf my land accuses me\n\tand all its furrows cry out together,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "or if I have stolen its crops\n\tor murdered its owners,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "then let thistles grow on that land instead of wheat,\n\tand weeds
        instead of barley.\u201D\n\tJob\u2019s words are ended."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Elihu Responds to Job\u2019s Friends"
      content: "Job\u2019s three friends refused to reply further to him because
        he kept insisting on his innocence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Elihu son of Barakel the Buzite, of the clan of Ram, became
        angry. He was angry because Job refused to admit that he had sinned and that
        God was right in punishing him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He was also angry with Job\u2019s three friends, for they made God[COMMENT[0]]
        appear to be wrong by their inability to answer Job\u2019s arguments. "
      comments:
      - number: '32:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in ancient Hebrew scribal tradition; the Masoretic Text reads '
          body: Job.
    - title: 
      content: 'Elihu had waited for the others to speak to Job because they were
        older than he. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But when he saw that they had no further reply, he spoke out angrily. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Elihu son of Barakel the Buzite said,\n\t\u201CI am young and you
        are old,\n\tso I held back from telling you what I think.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I thought, \u2018Those who are older should speak,\n\tfor wisdom
        comes with age.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But there is a spirit[COMMENT[0]] within people,\n\tthe breath of
        the Almighty within them,\n\tthat makes them intelligent.  "
      comments:
      - number: '32:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'Spirit; '
        - ft: also in 32:18.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Sometimes the elders are not wise.\n\tSometimes the aged do not understand
        justice.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So listen to me,\n\tand let me tell you what I think.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have waited all this time,\n\tlistening very carefully to
        your arguments,\n\tlistening to you grope for words.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have listened,\n\tbut not one of you has refuted Job\n\tor answered
        his arguments.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And don\u2019t tell me, \u2018He is too wise for us.\n\tOnly God
        can convince him.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If Job had been arguing with me,\n\tI would not answer with your
        kind of logic!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You sit there baffled,\n\twith nothing more to say.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Should I continue to wait, now that you are silent?\n\tMust I also
        remain silent?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No, I will say my piece.\n\tI will speak my mind.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I am full of pent-up words,\n\tand the spirit within me urges
        me on.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am like a cask of wine without a vent,\n\tlike a new wineskin ready
        to burst!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I must speak to find relief,\n\tso let me give my answers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I won\u2019t play favorites\n\tor try to flatter anyone.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For if I tried flattery,\n\tmy Creator would soon destroy me."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Elihu Presents His Case against Job
      content: "\u201CListen to my words, Job;\n\tpay attention to what I have to
        say.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now that I have begun to speak,\n\tlet me continue.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I speak with all sincerity;\n\tI speak the truth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the Spirit of God has made me,\n\tand the breath of the Almighty
        gives me life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Answer me, if you can;\n\tmake your case and take your stand.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look, you and I both belong to God.\n\tI, too, was formed from clay.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So you don\u2019t need to be afraid of me.\n\tI won\u2019t come down
        hard on you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou have spoken in my hearing,\n\tand I have heard your very
        words.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You said, \u2018I am pure; I am without sin;\n\tI am innocent; I
        have no guilt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God is picking a quarrel with me,\n\tand he considers me his enemy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He puts my feet in the stocks\n\tand watches my every move.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you are wrong, and I will show you why.\n\tFor God is greater
        than any human being.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So why are you bringing a charge against him?\n\tWhy say he does
        not respond to people\u2019s complaints?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For God speaks again and again,\n\tthough people do not recognize
        it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He speaks in dreams, in visions of the night,\n\twhen deep sleep
        falls on people\n\tas they lie in their beds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He whispers in their ears\n\tand terrifies them with warnings.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He makes them turn from doing wrong;\n\the keeps them from pride.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He protects them from the grave,\n\tfrom crossing over the river
        of death.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COr God disciplines people with pain on their sickbeds,\n\twith
        ceaseless aching in their bones.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They lose their appetite\n\tfor even the most delicious food.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their flesh wastes away,\n\tand their bones stick out.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are at death\u2019s door;\n\tthe angels of death wait for them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut if an angel from heaven appears\u2014\n\ta special messenger
        to intercede for a person\n\tand declare that he is upright\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "he will be gracious and say,\n\t\u2018Rescue him from the grave,\n\tfor
        I have found a ransom for his life.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
