        offspring.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their young grow up in the open fields,\n\tthen leave home and never
        return.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWho gives the wild donkey its freedom?\n\tWho untied its ropes?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have placed it in the wilderness;\n\tits home is the wasteland.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It hates the noise of the city\n\tand has no driver to shout at it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The mountains are its pastureland,\n\twhere it searches for every
        blade of grass.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWill the wild ox consent to being tamed?\n\tWill it spend the
        night in your stall?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can you hitch a wild ox to a plow?\n\tWill it plow a field for you?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Given its strength, can you trust it?\n\tCan you leave and trust
        the ox to do your work?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can you rely on it to bring home your grain\n\tand deliver it to
        your threshing floor?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe ostrich flaps her wings grandly,\n\tbut they are no match
        for the feathers of the stork.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She lays her eggs on top of the earth,\n\tletting them be warmed
        in the dust.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She doesn\u2019t worry that a foot might crush them\n\tor a wild
        animal might destroy them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She is harsh toward her young,\n\tas if they were not her own.\n\tShe
        doesn\u2019t care if they die.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For God has deprived her of wisdom.\n\tHe has given her no understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But whenever she jumps up to run,\n\tshe passes the swiftest horse
        with its rider.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave you given the horse its strength\n\tor clothed its neck
        with a flowing mane?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Did you give it the ability to leap like a locust?\n\tIts majestic
        snorting is terrifying!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It paws the earth and rejoices in its strength\n\twhen it charges
        out to battle.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It laughs at fear and is unafraid.\n\tIt does not run from the sword.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The arrows rattle against it,\n\tand the spear and javelin flash.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It paws the ground fiercely\n\tand rushes forward into battle when
        the ram\u2019s horn blows.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It snorts at the sound of the horn.\n\tIt senses the battle in the
        distance.\n\tIt quivers at the captain\u2019s commands and the noise of battle.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIs it your wisdom that makes the hawk soar\n\tand spread its
        wings toward the south?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Is it at your command that the eagle rises\n\tto the heights to make
        its nest?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It lives on the cliffs,\n\tmaking its home on a distant, rocky crag.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "From there it hunts its prey,\n\tkeeping watch with piercing eyes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Its young gulp down blood.\n\tWhere there\u2019s a carcass, there
        you\u2019ll find it.\u201D"
      comments: []
