  - verses:
    - title: Lord
      content: "Then Job replied to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI know that you can do anything,\n\tand no one can stop you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You asked, \u2018Who is this that questions my wisdom with such ignorance?\u2019\n\tIt
        is I\u2014and I was talking about things I knew nothing about,\n\tthings
        far too wonderful for me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You said, \u2018Listen and I will speak!\n\tI have some questions
        for you,\n\tand you must answer them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I had only heard about you before,\n\tbut now I have seen you with
        my own eyes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I take back everything I said,\n\tand I sit in dust and ashes to
        show my repentance.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: ' Blesses Job'
      content: "After the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had finished speaking to Job,
        he said to Eliphaz the Temanite: \u201CI am angry with you and your two friends,
        for you have not spoken accurately about me, as my servant Job has. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So take seven bulls and seven rams and go to my servant Job and offer
        a burnt offering for yourselves. My servant Job will pray for you, and I
        will accept his prayer on your behalf. I will not treat you as you deserve,
        for you have not spoken accurately about me, as my servant Job has.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Eliphaz the Temanite, Bildad the Shuhite, and Zophar the Naamathite
        did as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded them, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        accepted Job\u2019s prayer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When Job prayed for his friends, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        restored his fortunes. In fact, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave him
        twice as much as before! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then all his brothers, sisters, and former friends came and feasted
        with him in his home. And they consoled him and comforted him because of
        all the trials the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had brought against him. And
        each of them brought him a gift of money[COMMENT[0]] and a gold ring.  '
      comments:
